  <descriptors xsi:type="demo:MDemo" name="brd4116a.demo.ot-ncp-ftd-ble-rcp" label="Multiprotocol (OpenThread+BLE) - NCP" description="This multiprotocol Network Co-Processor (NCP) application enables concurrent OpenThread (Full Thread Device) and Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) connectivity. The OpenThread stack runs on the co-processor (NCP), while BLE operates as a controller, with its host stack running on the main processor.  This architecture leverages Silicon Labs multiprotocol capabilities for seamless mesh networking (Thread) and point-to-point wireless communication (BLE). Communication between host and NCP uses the Co-Processor Communication protocol (CPC), acting as a protocol multiplexer and serial transport layer.  Host applications connect to the CPC daemon, which in turn connects to the EFR device via UART or EUSART. Refer to *docs.silabs.com Multiprotocol section - Multiprotocol on Linux Solution: Running Thread and Bluetooth Concurrently on a Linux Host with a Multiprotocol Network Co-Processor* for more information on host/co-processor integration and multiprotocol use cases. ">
